Thomas William Higginson, MBE (born 6 November 1936 in Esher, Surrey) is an English former first-class cricketer. 
Known as Bill, he represented Middlesex in three first-class matches and once for L. C. Stevens XI in 1960.He later served as a scorer and umpire. In later years, he was subsequently awarded the MBE for his community service.
